@page
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Playbooks";
    var signedIn = User?.Identity?.IsAuthenticated == true;
}

<section class="product-page product-page--immersive">
    <header class="page-hero immersive-hero">
        <div class="section-stack">
            <span class="hero-kicker">Use-case playbooks</span>
            <div>
                <span class="section-eyebrow">Scenario library</span>
                <h1>Playbooks for onboarding, support and software rollout conversations</h1>
                <p>This page helps propagate the product. Instead of only describing pages, it shows how NestStats can be positioned and used during real customer, installer and admin workflows.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="hero-actions">
                <a class="button button--primary" asp-page="@(signedIn ? "/Index" : "/SpoznajNas")">@(signedIn ? "Back to workspace" : "Back to overview")</a>
                <a class="button button--ghost" href="https://github.com/PavolLukacka/NestStats/blob/main/NESTSTATS_TECHNICAL_DOCUMENTATION.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open technical documentation</a>
            </div>
        </div>
        <aside class="hero-note hero-note--signal">
            <strong>Playbook intent</strong>
            <span>Use these narratives when you need the software to sound like a complete solution, not only a technical interface.</span>
        </aside>
    </header>

    <div class="story-grid">
        <article class="story-card">
            <strong>Playbook 1: New residential install</strong>
            <ul class="number-list">
                <li>Create the account and complete Launch with a clean home or client identity.</li>
                <li>Attach the installation in Systems and define the customer-friendly alias.</li>
                <li>Set the tariff and primary site in Settings so the dashboard story becomes financially meaningful.</li>
            </ul>
        </article>
        <article class="story-card story-card--cool">
            <strong>Playbook 2: Support rescue</strong>
            <ul class="number-list">
                <li>Admin checks the overview for users with no systems or incomplete onboarding.</li>
                <li>Use the assignment desk to bind the system centrally when the customer is blocked.</li>
                <li>Send the customer back to the dashboard with a live, coherent workspace instead of a half-configured shell.</li>
            </ul>
        </article>
    </div>

    <section class="module-grid">
        <article class="module-card module-card--accent">
            <span class="section-eyebrow">Sales framing</span>
            <h3>Lead with operating clarity</h3>
            <p>Position NestStats as the layer that connects field telemetry with decisions, economics and support handoff.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="module-card">
            <span class="section-eyebrow">Installer framing</span>
            <h3>Reduce handoff friction</h3>
            <p>The product helps installers move from physical completion into digital completion without losing customer context.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="module-card signal-card--cool">
            <span class="section-eyebrow">Support framing</span>
            <h3>Service without spreadsheet chaos</h3>
            <p>Admin views, assignments and product documentation keep support actions in the same shell as the operational product.</p>
        </article>
    </section>
</section>
